Revised to_map function. Itâ€™s more convenient for testing to handle Geojson conversion with geopandas instead of PostGIS.

QUEENS = [40.7292, -73.9049]

def to_map(result_set, location=QUEENS, geom_col='geom', epsg=4326, zoom=13, fillcolor='orange'):
    m = folium.Map(location=location, zoom_start=zoom)
    df = result_set.DataFrame()
    gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame(df, geometry=gpd.GeoSeries.from_wkb(df[geom_col], crs=epsg))

    if epsg != 4326:
        gdf.to_crs(4326, inplace=True)

    geojson = json.loads(gdf.to_json())

    for r in geojson['features']:

        if 'properties' in r.keys():
            properties = r['properties']
        else:
            properties = None

        popup_cols = [c for c in properties.keys() if geom_col not in c.lower()] if properties is not None else []
        geo_j = folium.GeoJson(data=r,
                                style_function=lambda x: {'fillColor': fillcolor},
                                popup=folium.GeoJsonPopup(popup_cols)
        )
        geo_j.add_to(m)

    return m

New York Restaurants#

All New York restaurants including county FIPS code, county name

%%sql 
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS restaurants_ny;

CREATE TABLE restaurants_ny AS
SELECT rt.name, ct.countyfp, ct.name as county_name, rt.geom FROM restaurants rt
JOIN cb_2020_ny_county_500k ct
ON ST_Within(rt.geom, ST_Transform(ct.geom, 4326));

 * postgresql+psycopg2://docker:***@0.0.0.0:25432/restaurants
Done.

Number of restaurants, McDonalds count, Pizza Hunt count, and most common restaurants within New York counties

%%sql county_rt <<
SELECT ct.countyfp, ct.name,
COUNT(rt.*) as rt_num, 
COUNT(rt.name) FILTER (where rt.name = 'MCD') as mcd_num, 
COUNT(rt.name) FILTER (where rt.name = 'PZH') as pzh_num, 
mode() WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY rt.name) AS rt_most,
ct.geom
FROM restaurants rt
JOIN cb_2020_ny_county_500k ct
ON ST_Within(rt.geom, ST_Transform(ct.geom, 4326))
GROUP BY ct.countyfp, ct.name, ct.geom;

Find the number of restaurants within 200, 500, and 1000 meters of McDonalds in Queens. Long Island State Plane (EPSG: 32118) is used to Proximity Distance Query.

%%sql mcd_proximity <<
WITH rt_qns AS (
    SELECT 
        rt.id,
        rt.name,
        ct.countyfp, 
        ct.name as county_name,
        rt.geom
    FROM restaurants rt
    JOIN cb_2020_ny_county_500k ct
    ON ST_Within(rt.geom, ST_Transform(ct.geom, 4326))
    WHERE 
        ct.countyfp = '081' 
),
mcd_qns AS (
    SELECT *
    FROM rt_qns
    WHERE rt_qns.name = 'MCD'
),
rt_200 AS (
    SELECT
    mcd_qns.id, 
    count(rt_qns.*) as rt_200
    FROM mcd_qns as mcd_qns, rt_qns as rt_qns
    WHERE ST_DWithin(ST_Transform(mcd_qns.geom, 32118), ST_Transform(rt_qns.geom, 32118), 200)
    GROUP BY mcd_qns.geom, mcd_qns.name, mcd_qns.id
),
rt_500 AS (
    SELECT
    mcd_qns.id,
    count(rt_qns.*) as rt_500
    FROM mcd_qns as mcd_qns, rt_qns as rt_qns
    WHERE ST_DWithin(ST_Transform(mcd_qns.geom, 32118), ST_Transform(rt_qns.geom, 32118), 500)
    GROUP BY mcd_qns.geom, mcd_qns.name, mcd_qns.id
),
rt_1000 AS (
    SELECT
    mcd_qns.id, mcd_qns.name, 
    count(rt_qns.*) as rt_1000, mcd_qns.geom
    FROM mcd_qns as mcd_qns, rt_qns as rt_qns
    WHERE ST_DWithin(ST_Transform(mcd_qns.geom, 32118), ST_Transform(rt_qns.geom, 32118), 1000)
    GROUP BY mcd_qns.geom, mcd_qns.name, mcd_qns.id
)
SELECT rt_1000.id, rt_1000.name, rt_200.rt_200, rt_500.rt_500, rt_1000.rt_1000, rt_1000.geom
FROM 
rt_200 JOIN rt_500 ON rt_200.id = rt_500.id JOIN rt_1000 ON rt_1000.id = rt_500.id;
